article.headline: North Texas 72, Louisiana-Lafayette 65
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Quincy Williams scored 18 points and grabbed seven rebounds to lead North Texas past Louisiana-Lafayette 72-65 on Saturday night. The Ragin' Cajuns took a 65-64 lead on Randell Daigle's 3-pointer with 3:59 remaining. But the Mean Green (12-4, 3-2 Sun Belt) went on an 8-0 run to close out the game. Collin Dennis scored 17 points, making eight of nine free throws for North Texas. Ben Bell, who tied the score on a 3-pointer to beat the halftime buzzer, finished with seven points and six assists. The Mean Green held a 35-27 edge on the boards. Daigle scored a career-high 17 points, with 15 coming on 3-pointers. He added four assists for the Ragin' Cajuns (7-9, 4-2). Abray Milson had 10 points and six rebounds.
